Input.name: Economy of Belarus
Input.question1: Which field of employment contributes the most to the Belarusian economy based on 2015 estimate?
Input.question2: What was the most imported and exported goods from Belarus based on 2017 estimates?
Input.question3: How many parties does Joe’s Biden’s is associated with in his entire lifetime?
Answer.Ans3: The United States Senator from Delaware, Chair of the International Narcotics Control Caucus, Chair of Senate Foreign Relations Committee
Answer.Res1: Based on the 2015 estimate, services contribute 66.8% to the Belarusian economy based on 2015 estimate. As no other field of employment contributes more than or equal to 66.8%, the field of employment contributes the most to the Belarusian economy based on the 2015 estimate is services.
Answer.Res2: Based on 2017 estimates, Manufacturers formed 55.0% of Export goods and Manufacturers formed 51.5% of Import goods. As Manufacturers occupy the highest place in Export goods as well as Import goods, the most imported and exported goods from Belarus based on 2017 estimates was Manufacturers.
Answer.Res3: Joe Biden served as the United States Senator from Delaware from January 3, 1973, to January 15, 2009. In 2008, he was also serving as the Chair of the International Narcotics Control Caucus (2007-2009) and Chair of the Senate Foreign Relations Committee (2007-2009, and previously 2001-2003).
